definitions: any of a number of different organs through which the silk, gossamer, or thread of spiders, silkworms, and certain other insects is produced.
shortDefinitions: several different organs through which silk, gossamer, or thread of spiders, silkworms, and certain other insects is produced

definitions: (in the production of man-made fibers) a cap or plate with a number of small holes through which a fiber-forming solution is forced.
shortDefinitions: (in production of man-made fibres) cap or plate with several small holes through which fibre-forming solution is forced
